File: Rugby balls LONDON - The Blitzboks started their London Sevens campaign on a high note. Four tries to three saw them beat Argentina 26-19. READ: New Zealand sparkle on World Rugby Sevens Series return Dewald Human opened the scoring against last week’s fifth place finishers. The South Americans have improved over the years in this format of the game. The speedsters dominated proceedings with a gem by Marcos Moneta providing a tense finish. Angelo Davids ran in the winning try to hand Neil Powell’s men a needed boost. 